Mass grave: On 17 February 2020 a mass grave of 65 civilians and regime fighters was found in the area of Al A'ab Farms south-east of Duma city in Rural Damascus. The civilians and fighters were reportedly abducted and killed by opposition factions in 2014 when the area was under the control of Jaysh al Islam.

On 17 February 2020 Russian warplanes carried out airstrikes on Daret Azza and its surroundings in Aleppo. The strikes targeted Al-Kenana hospital south of Daret Azza partially destroying the hospital building and causing intermediate damage to its equipment and furniture which put the hospital out of service. Al-Firdaws Hospital in the same area was also targeted by Russian airstrikes. The strikes resulted in the wounding of one of the hospital's medical staff as well as extensive damage to the hospital building and equipment. No fatalities were reported.

Airstrikes on the 91 Brigade near Kisweh the 75 Brigade near Al-Muqaylabiyah the Baghdad Bridge area and the agricultural airport in the vicinity of Izra'a in Dar'a resulted in the killing of 15 pro-Iran militias including at least 3 Iranians.
